[1] Global, 5 WPV1, 20 cVDPV - GPEI/WHO
Date: 28 Nov 2019
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus weekly update, as of 27 Nov 2019, WHO
------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 5
Environment: 0
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 20
Environment: 8
Others: 0

Headlines
Summary of new viruses this week (AFP cases and ES positives):
Pakistan - 5 WPV1 cases, 2 cVDPV2 cases and 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample;
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo) - 5 cVDPV2 cases;
Benin - 4 cVDPV2 cases;
Ghana - 4 cVDPV2 cases and 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples;
Philippines - 3 cVDPV2 cases and 5 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples;
Togo - 2 cVDPV2 cases.

Afghanistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported this week. There are 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.

Pakistan
- 5 wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) cases were reported: 1 each from Shaheed Benazirabad, Jamshoro and Karachi Kamari in Sindh province and 1 each from Bannu and Lakki Marwat in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. The onsets of paralysis were between [9 Oct 2019] and [7 Nov 2019]. There are now 91 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 12 WPV1 cases in 2018.
- 2 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) cases were reported from Kohistan in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. The onsets of paralysis were [11 and 27 Oct 2019]. There are 11 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019.
- 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported from Diamer in Gilgit province. The sample was collected on [16 Oct 2019].

Nigeria
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. 18 cVDPV2 cases have been reported in 2019. There were 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2018.

Chad
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case in the country linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Benin
- 4 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week: 1 each from Natitingou in Atacora province, Parakou in Borgou province, Bante in Collines and Djougou in Donga province. The onsets of paralysis were between [21 Sep 2019] and [15 Oct 2019]. There are 6 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Ghana
- 4 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week: 1 each from Savelugu in Northern province, Sunyani Municipal in Bono province, Nkwanta South Municipal in Oti province and Gonja central in Savannah province. The onsets of paralysis were between [8 and 23 Oct 2019]. There are 9 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.
- 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported from Ayawaso East Municipal in the Greater Accra province. The samples were collected on [23 Oct 2019].
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- 5 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week: 3 from Koshibanda in Kwilu province and 1 from Popokabaka in Kwango province. The onsets of paralysis were between [22 Sep 2019] and [7 Oct 2019]. There are 50 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 and 20 in 2018.

Angola
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 42 cVDPV2 cases from 7 outbreaks reported in 2019.

Central African Republic:
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 16 reported cases in 2019 from 6 different outbreaks of cVDPV2 in 2019.

Côte d'Ivoire
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week.

Togo
- 2 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week from Oti in Savanes province. The onsets of paralysis were on [6 and 16 Oct 2019] respectively. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in 2019 in the country linked to Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.

Zambia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case from the 1st outbreak in the country.

Horn of Africa
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in Ethiopia in 2019, all linked to the outbreak in neighbouring Somalia.
- Somalia has reported a total of 15 cVDPV cases (8 type 2, 6 type 3 and 1 coinfection of both type 2 and type 3) since the beginning of the outbreaks. The most recent cVDPV3 virus was from an AFP case from Runingod district, Middle Shabelle province with an onset date of paralysis on [7 Sep 2018]. Circulating VDPV2 has also been detected during 2018 in one environmental sample in Kenya collected on [21 Mar 2018].

Papua New Guinea
- No new cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported this week. There were 26 cases reported in 2018. It has now been 1 year since the country has had a cVDPV1 case.

Mozambique
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was been reported this week. There was 1 case reported in 2018.

Indonesia
- No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) cases were reported this week. 1 cVDPV1 case was reported in 2018 from Papua province with onset of paralysis on [28 Nov 2018].
- This outbreak is not linked to the cVDPV1 in neighbouring Papua New Guinea.

Iran
- No new WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported this week. In total, 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, all from Sistan and Balochistan province. The isolated viruses have been detected in environmental samples only, and genetic sequencing confirms they are linked to WPV1 circulating in Karachi, Pakistan.

China
- No cVDPV2 cases were reported this week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in the country remains one.

Myanmar
- No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) cases were reported this week. There are 6 reported cases of cVDPV1 in 2019.

Philippines
- 3 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) cases were reported this week: 2 from Maguindanao in the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao and 1 in South Cotabato in Southern Mindanao. The onsets of paralysis were between [25 Sep 2019] and [2 Oct 2019]. There are 6 reported cases of cVDPV2 in 2019.
- 5 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported from Manila in the National Capital Region. The samples were collected between [19 and 22 Oct 2019].

